"Velichko A.A., Morozova T.D.","Paleopedological approach to evaluation of soil response to anthropogenic global warming",1996,"Eurasian Soil Science","29","1",,"42","47",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-3042904076&partnerID=40&md5=f368aa9154eaa82e9cb36d4b0530ff1c","Institute of Geography, Russian Academy of Sciences, Staromonetnyi per. 29, Moscow, 109017, Russian Federation","Velichko, A.A., Institute of Geography, Russian Academy of Sciences, Staromonetnyi per. 29, Moscow, 109017, Russian Federation; Morozova, T.D., Institute of Geography, Russian Academy of Sciences, Staromonetnyi per. 29, Moscow, 109017, Russian Federation","Buried soils contain information which may be used to forecast soil changes related to global climate warming. Average global warming by 0.8-1°C corresponds to the Holocene thermic optimum (5500-6000 years ago) and warming by 1.8-2.0°C corresponds to the last Mikulino interglacial optimum (125 000 years ago). The reconstructions are regarded only as an element of the forecast. Drafts of scenarios are suggested for Eastern Europe in case of global warming, taking into account equilibrium and non-equilibrium pedogenic models.",,,,,,,,"Velichko, A.A., Response of the Landscape Sphere to Global Climatic Changes (1991) Izv. Akad. Nauk SSSR, Ser. Geogr., (5); Velichko, A.A., Morozova, T.D., Soil Cover of Miculino Interglacial and Bryansk Interval (maps 7, 8) (1982) Paleogeografiya Evropy za Poslednie Sto Tysyach Let (Paleogeography of Europe in the Last 100 000 Years), , Moscow: Nauka; Velichko, A.A., Morozova, T.D., Evolution of Pedogenesis in Terms of Paleogeography (1985) Pochvovedenie, (11), pp. 76-86; Velichko, A.A., Karpachevskii, L.O., Morozova, T.D., Water Content of Soils in Case of Global Warming: A Forecasting Draft by Example of Eastern Europe (1995) Pochvovedenie, (8), pp. 933-942; Gerasimov, I.P., Ancient Soils and Eluvial Formations, and Their Meaning for Paleogeography of the Quaternary (1946) Tr. Inst. Geogr.